# Nemotron 3 Super 120B A12B (Q2_K) — Optimal config for 3x Intel Arc A770
# Benchmarked 2026-03-14: 4.56 t/s gen, 4.08 t/s prompt (127% over baseline)
#
# Key optimizations:
#   1. GGML_SYCL_DISABLE_GRAPH=0  — SYCL graph recording for pipelined dispatch (+56%)
#   2. ffn_down_exps offload only  — keep ffn_up on GPU, offload ffn_down to CPU (+7%)
#      (offloading ffn_up instead is 34% SLOWER — serializes the pipeline)
#   3. Flash attention (-fa on)    — faster attention kernels (+3%)
#   4. Single slot (-np 1)         — frees ~500 MiB recurrent state (+0.4%)
#
# VRAM usage: ~24.5 GB / 48 GB (model 21.5 GB + overhead 3 GB)
# CPU RAM:    ~30 GB (ffn_down_exps for 40 MoE layers)
# Model:      51 GB total, 40 MoE layers with 512 experts (22 active/token)

MODEL_PATH=/home/ryan/llm-stack/models/NVIDIA/Nemotron-3-Super-120B-A12B-GGUF/nvidia_Nemotron-3-Super-120B-A12B-Q2_K/nvidia_Nemotron-3-Super-120B-A12B-Q2_K-00001-of-00002.gguf
SPLIT_MODE=layer
N_GPU_LAYERS=999
TENSOR_SPLIT=1,1,1
OVERRIDE_TENSOR=blk\.\d+\.ffn_down_exps\.weight=CPU
CONTEXT_SIZE=2048
FLASH_ATTN=on
N_PARALLEL=1

# Environment variables (set before launching server)
GGML_SYCL_DISABLE_GRAPH=0
